Yesterday we celebrated the life of our dear Grammie with a beautiful church service at her beloved St. Wilfred’s, laid her to rest next to Grampie, shared stories with those lucky enough to know her and went to back to her house, a house filled with so many memories over the decades, for one last family gathering. We cried, we laughed, we reminisced, we danced, we healed, we loved. It was the perfect day honoring our Grammie. 

1. The Fam
2. Church 
3. Beautiful thoughts from Grammie
4. Cousin Zach’s tattoos honoring Grammie and his Mother (Aunt Patti)
5. Grammie’s See’s Candy order 
6. Story time going through her jewelry 
7. Zach’s new jewelry (and new personality)
8. My new necklace - we saw a butterfly in the church courtyard, saw more at her house and sure enough I found this necklace 🦋
9. Cousin Performances 🎤
10. Grammie ❤️
